          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-06 16:48:39" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the part of the leg below the ankle on which a person or animal stands and moves</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>foot</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:06601000100056} (οἱ πόδες αὐτοῦ ὡς στῦλοι πυρός ‘his feet were like pillars of fire’) it is possible that πούς refers to the leg since the context of {S:06601000100056} would seem to favor this interpretation, but the meaning of ‘foot’ should not be excluded, especially since this passage refers to an image as part of a supernatural vision, and one cannot be certain of the specific intent.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
