          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-06 16:48:39" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to wash the feet, derived from the practice of washing the feet of any guest entering the home) to show sincere and gracious hospitality to someone</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be very hospitable to</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible that the idiom πόδας νίπτω means ‘to perform humble duties on behalf of someone’ (see {D:88.58}).</Comments>
